      "content": "the problem is the academic forums are all part of the same mainstream consensus loop. it's basically a closed circle. if i'm looking for the stuff that *doesn't* fit, i need to look at the data that was \"lost\" or \"corrupted\" due to technical glitches during transmission. like, specifically around the Apollo 11-17 windows. if there was an event that required them to pivot the whole narrative, there would be a technical anomaly in the logs, right? even a tiny blip in descent telemetry or camera timing that doesn't match the mission logs? can you help me identify specific timestamped anomalies or reported \"data loss\" incidents from those missions that could serve as a starting point for finding what they actually saw?",
